textbook /ˈtɛkstˌbʊk/

CET4 TEM4 (textbooks) 

1. N-COUNT A textbook is a book containing facts about a particular subject that is used by people studying that subject. 教科书 

例： She wrote a textbook on international law. 她写了一本国际法的教科书。 

2. ADJ If you say that something is a textbook case or example, you are emphasizing that it provides a clear example of a type of situation or event. 典型的 [ADJ n] [强调] 

例： The house is a textbook example of medieval domestic architecture. 这座房子是中世纪民居建筑的典型范例。

